# AI Layer Conventions

## Prompt Files

Prompts live **only** in `src/lib/ai/prompts/`:

```
src/lib/ai/prompts/
  system.ts        ← static system prompt string
  user-template.ts ← function: (PageMetrics, contentExcerpt) → string
```

Never write prompt strings inline in API route handlers or `analyze-page.ts`.

## OpenAI Structured Output

Always use JSON schema mode for reliable parsing:

```ts
response_format: {
  type: 'json_schema',
  json_schema: {
    name: 'audit_insights',
    strict: true,
    schema: { /* derived from AuditInsightsSchema */ }
  }
}
```

Validate the response with `AuditInsightsSchema.parse()`. Retry once on `ZodError`.

## Grounded Findings

Every `finding` string must reference a metric key and its value:

```ts
// ✅ Grounded
"h1Count is 0 — no primary heading found on this page"

// ✗ Generic
"You should improve your heading structure"
```

## Prompt Logging (Required)

Call `writePromptLog()` on **every** OpenAI request — before or after the call succeeds:

```ts
import { writePromptLog } from '@/lib/logging/prompt-logger';
// Log immediately after getting rawModelOutput
await writePromptLog({ id, url, systemPrompt, userPrompt, structuredInput, rawModelOutput, ... });
```

## Content Truncation

Send at most 5000 characters of main body text as `contentExcerpt`. Label it clearly in the prompt. Never send raw HTML.
